  "text": "One application of our main result is the study of Bridgeland's stability spaces of triangulated categories [CITATION_1] . Basing on the work of Qiu and Woolf [QW] , we apply Theorem 1.1 to give sufficient conditions on the contractibility of the stability space of a triangulated category D. In Example 3.15 we will give some known examples where K b (projΛ) is silting-discrete. By Theorem 1.3(b), Example 3.15(2) affirms the first part of [CITATION_2] Conjecture 5.8] . During the preparation of this work, we were informed by Pauktztello, Saorín and Zvonareva that they independently obtained Theorem 1.3(b) in [PSZ] .",
